Taraba State Governor, Darius Ishaku, has imposed a curfew on Jalingo, following fresh outbreak of crisis in some communities in Kona and ATC areas of the city. This was contained in a statement by the Senior Special Assistant to the Governor on Media and Publicity, Mr. Bala Dan Abu.
According to the statement, the curfew would run from 4p.m. to 6a.m. daily till further notice. “In view of the fresh outbreak of crisis in some communities in Kona and ATC near Jalingo, the Taraba State government has decided to impose a curfew on Jalingo and all the affected communities with immediate effect.
“The curfew is from 4p.m. to 6a.m. daily and it remains in force until further notice,” it stated. The statement further noted that security agencies in the state had been directed to strictly enforce the curfew to ensure compliance and quick return of peace to the affected communities.